          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Is Curriculum Learning?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Curriculum learning (Bengio et al. 2009) is the strategy of ordering training examples so that the model encounters easier examples first and progressively harder examples later — mirroring how humans and animals learn. For language models, curriculum ordering applies at two levels:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Data ordering (pre-training):",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " arrange tokens or documents from simpler to more complex across the training run. Phi-1 (2023) trained a 1.3B model to match 350B-parameter models by focusing entirely on 'textbook quality' code — a form of difficulty-based selection applied from the start."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Task ordering (instruction fine-tuning):",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " arrange instruction-response pairs by task difficulty, routing the model through increasingly complex reasoning chains before exposing it to competition-level problems."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
