        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Curriculum learning improves training efficiency and final model quality by controlling the order in which the model sees examples. Competence-based curricula sort the full dataset once by a difficulty proxy and train with a growing data window. Self-paced learning adapts continuously to the model's current loss without pre-scoring. Domain mixing schedules implement implicit curriculum in pre-training by shifting from broad web data to curated, high-quality sources late in the run."
